From a88f6696fa38303236549ebc102a4879e62feb6f Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Luis Diego Rodriguez <ldrodriguezr@users.noreply.github.com>
Date: Wed, 13 May 2026 01:52:29 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] =?UTF-8?q?feat:=20quick-create=20inline,=20bulk=20actions?=
 =?UTF-8?q?,=20=E2=8C=98K=20command=20palette,=20calendar=20view,=20GitHub?=
 =?UTF-8?q?=20sync?=
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

- Quick-create inline: click 'Add issue' in any Board column opens an inline textarea
  (Enter to create, Esc to cancel) instead of opening the full modal

- Bulk actions in Backlog: checkbox on each row (visible on hover), floating toolbar
  at bottom when items selected — bulk move to sprint, set status, set priority

- Command palette (⌘K / Ctrl+K): global search overlay accessible from sidebar or
  keyboard — navigate pages, switch projects, search issues by title/ticket ID

- Calendar view: new /calendar page with monthly grid showing all issues with
  due_date; click any issue to open IssueModal; Today button + prev/next navigation

- GitHub sync: per-project GitHub settings in Projects page (owner, repo, token),
  syncs open PRs and/or issues as Jira tasks; tracks already-synced items to avoid
  duplicates; shows created/skipped count after sync

- Migration 004_github_sync.sql: github_settings + github_sync_items tables
